   <text>
      <body>
         <head>To <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0763.xml"/>the Rev. Samuel
            Furly</persName></head>
         <opener><placeName>Yarm</placeName><lb/><date when="1759-07-07">July 7, 1759</date><lb/><lb/>
            <salute>Dear Sammy,</salute>
         </opener>
         <p><pb n="168"/>Our Conference at <placeName>Leeds</placeName> is to begin on <date
               when="1759-08-01">Wednesday, August 1</date>. I hope to see you at it.<note
               place="foot" n="1">There is no record that <persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers0763.xml"/>Furly</persName> attended this or any of the
               Conferences. While repeatedly courted by <persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>, he did not become active in the
               Methodist connexion.</note> If you are in <placeName>Yorkshire</placeName> some days
            sooner, we shall have more time together. Your present call to
               <placeName>Kippax</placeName> is clear.<note place="foot" n="2"><persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers0763.xml"/>Furly</persName> was preparing to move from
                  <placeName>Lakenheath</placeName> to <placeName>Kippax, Yorkshire</placeName>,
               still as curate. He would come to know Lady <persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers0964.xml"/>Huntingdon</persName> while at
                  <placeName>Kippax</placeName>.</note> When you are called farther, that will be
            clear also.</p>
         <p>What avails all knowledge but that which ministers to the knowledge of Christ, and which
            qualifies us for saving our own souls and the souls of them that hear us? What knowledge
            you have of other things retain, but secure this in all and above all. I am, with love
            to <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0761.xml"/>Nancy</persName>, dear <persName><ref
                  target="/persons/pers0763.xml"/>Sammy</persName>,</p>
         <closer><signed>Yours affectionately,<lb/><persName>J. Wesley</persName></signed></closer>
      </body>
   </text>
